com.apriori.util

Class Variable<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.apriori.util.Variable<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type value held by this variable
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class Variable<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    A simple variable reference. This can be useful for simulating "out" parameters to a function or for simulating non-final values being mutated from within an anonymous class or lambda. This is lighter-weight than using a single element array as the container and provides an API that is easier to read.

    In many respects, this is similar to an Atom except that it is not thread-safe. If the variable is being accessed from multiple threads, use an Atom or an AtomicReference.
